# Copy this file to `.env.local` in your project root and uncomment only the
# variables your project actually uses.
#
# Each variable is grouped by:
# - Used by: which portable skills/workflows read it
# - Set to: what kind of value to provide
#
# Path guidance:
# - If your project vendors the canonical skills from this repo, prefer `./skills/...`
# - If your project installs skills into harness-specific directories, point at that
#   installed copy instead (for example `.agents/skills/...` or `.claude/skills/...`)
#
# `skills/worktree` symlinks `.env.local` into worktrees, so these settings stay
# available in delegated sessions.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════
# WORKTREE / SHARED WORKFLOW PATHS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════

# WORKTREE_DEFAULT_BRANCH="main"
# Used by: worktree, orchestration
# Set to: your repo's main integration branch if auto-detection is not reliable.

# WORKTREE_SYMLINKS=".cache benchmarks/results"
# Used by: worktree
# Set to: space-separated project-relative paths that should stay shared across worktrees.

# WORKTREE_COPIES=".tooling/settings.json"
# Used by: worktree
# Set to: space-separated project-relative files that should be copied into each worktree.

# ISSUE_CLI="./skills/linear/scripts/linear.sh"
# Used by: linear, issue-lifecycle, orchestration, project-management
# Set to: the issue tracker CLI command your workflows should call.
# If you use the bundled Linear skill, `./skills/linear/scripts/linear.sh` is the canonical path.

# GIT_HOST_CLI="./skills/github/scripts/github.sh"
# Used by: github, orchestration
# Set to: the Git host CLI command your workflows should call.
# If you use the bundled GitHub skill, `./skills/github/scripts/github.sh` is the canonical path.

# WORKTREE_CLI="./skills/worktree/scripts/worktree"
# Used by: worktree, orchestration
# Set to: the worktree management command your workflows should call.

# VALIDATE_CMD="./tools/validate --quick"
# Used by: issue-lifecycle, orchestration
# Set to: your repo's main build/test/lint entrypoint.
# This command should work from the project root and ideally support quick/full/recheck modes if your repo uses them.

# DIFF_SUMMARY_CMD="./tools/git-diff-summary"
# Used by: issue-lifecycle, orchestration
# Set to: an optional diff summarizer that groups changed files by subsystem or risk.

# DECISIONS_CMD="./skills/decider/scripts/decisions.sh"
# Used by: issue-lifecycle, orchestration
# Set to: an optional project decision lookup/create command.

# ORCH_STATE_DIR="tmp"
# Used by: orchestration
# Set to: an alternate directory for persisted orchestration workflow state.

# HARNESS_CMD="codex exec --issue {issue}"
# Used by: orchestration (`parallel-launch`)
# Set to: an optional command template that launches a harness session for a given issue.
# Include `{issue}` where the issue ID should be inserted.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════
# BOT / COMMIT IDENTITY
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════

# BOT_NAME="automation-bot"
# Used by: worktree
# Set to: the git user.name to use inside bot-created worktrees.

# BOT_EMAIL="you+bot@example.com"
# Used by: worktree
# Set to: the git user.email to use inside bot-created worktrees.

# BOT_SIGNING_KEY="ssh-ed25519 AAAA..."
# Used by: worktree
# Set to: an optional SSH signing key for commits made inside worktrees.

# BOT_REMOTE_NAME="bot-remote"
# Used by: worktree
# Set to: the git remote name to use for bot pushes.

# BOT_REMOTE_URL="git@github-bot:org/repo.git"
# Used by: worktree
# Set to: the git remote URL to add to worktrees when bot pushes should use a separate remote.

# BOT_REVIEWERS="review-bot-a[bot],review-bot-b[bot]"
# Used by: github, orchestration
# Set to: comma-separated review bot usernames when review waiting should not rely on auto-detection.

# BOT_CHECK_NAME="review-bot"
# Used by: orchestration (`bot-review-wait`)
# Set to: an optional CI check name that signals bot review progress early.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════
# LINEAR
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════

# LINEAR_API_KEY="lin_api_..."
# Used by: linear
# Set to: a Linear personal API key from Linear Settings -> API.

# LINEAR_TEAM="MyTeam"
# Used by: linear
# Set to: the default Linear team name your issue commands should target.

# LINEAR_FORMAT="safe"
# Used by: linear
# Set to: the default output format for the Linear CLI (`safe`, `table`, `ids`, or `raw`).

# LINEAR_TEAM_PREFIX="PROJ"
# Used by: linear
# Set to: the issue ID prefix used by your team, such as `PROJ` for `PROJ-123`.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════
# GITHUB
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════

# GH_BOT_TOKEN="ghp_..."
# Used by: github
# Set to: a GitHub token for bot PR/comment/review actions.
# Can also be a 1Password reference if your environment provides `op`.

# GH_BOT_USERNAME="automation[bot]"
# Used by: github
# Set to: the GitHub login that should be treated as the review/comment bot.

# GH_ISSUE_PATTERN="[A-Z]+-[0-9]+"
# Used by: github, orchestration
# Set to: the regex used to extract issue IDs from branch names.

# GH_VERIFY_CMD="make verify"
# Used by: github (`pr-cross-check --verify`)
# Set to: the command that should run for full verification if auto-detection is not enough.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════
# BENCHMARKING
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════

# BENCH_CLI="./skills/benchmarking/scripts/bench.sh"
# Used by: issue-lifecycle (QA/perf paths)
# Set to: an optional benchmarking CLI for baseline capture, regression checks, and result recording.

# BENCH_PARSER="./tools/parse-bench-output"
# Used by: issue-lifecycle (QA/perf paths)
# Set to: an optional parser that converts your benchmark output into the format expected by `BENCH_CLI record`.
